The 2019 Abuja International Trade Fair (2019 AITF) organised by the Abuja Chamber of Commerce and Industry (ACCI) will end today. A statement signed by the Chairman of the Planning Committee,  Dr. Johnson Anene and the Director General, Tonia Shoyele, said the fair was extended from ending on Sunday, September 29, 2019. He noted that the extension became necessary in view of popular demand by exhibitors. He said, “We decided to take advantage of the upcoming National Independence public holiday to allow residents participate actively in the Fair. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY “Our aim of organising this Fair is to ensure that the subscribers and other categories of stakeholders maximally take advantage of this platform,” the statement said. The Daily Trust observed that the Abuja International Trade and Convention Centre, where the Fair is taking place has been a beehive of activities as innovators,  service providers,  distributors,  buyers and sellers,  foreign countries as well as Ministries, Departments and Agencies (MDAs) are actively participating in the 2019 AITF. 25 countries for Kano int’l trade fair Trade Fair: FG pledges to strengthen trade support infrastructure Local, foreign participants kick over low sales as Lagos fair closes today